# UI Conventions

## Use core widgets, not raw Material

Import from `package:hondana/core/core.dart`:

- `AppScaffold` not `Scaffold`, `AppAppBar` not `AppBar`,
  `AppText.<style>('key')` not `Text`.
- Load states: `AppLoadingIndicator`, `AppEmptyIndicator(message:)`,
  `AppFailureIndicator(message:, onRetry:)`.
- `PageLayoutBuilder(mobile: ...)` wraps a page's responsive content.

## Pages are thin compositions

A page provides its Bloc and returns `AppScaffold(appBar:, body:)` whose body is
a composition of **extracted widget classes** from `presentation/widgets/`.
Extract a section to its own class when reused, substantial (own layout/state),
or needed for readability — otherwise keep it a private `_Widget` in the same
file. Don't explode a screen into dozens of micro-widget files.

## Theming

Colors come from `context.colorScheme.*` — never hardcoded hex in shared widgets.
Text styles from `AppText.<style>` / `context.textTheme`. Dark mode has a
pure-black variant (`AppTheme.dark(pureBlack:)`) driven by
`AppSettings.pureBlackNotifier`. RTL via `context.isRtl`.

## Sizing — flutter_screenutil

Every length scaled: `16.w`, `16.h`, `12.r`, `12.sp`, `16.verticalSpace`. No raw
size literals (see `flutter-guardrails.mdc`). Never `double.infinity` — use
`context.width` / `context.height`.

## Localization — no hardcoded strings

Route every user-facing string through `easy_localization` with a nested dotted
key in `assets/translations/en.json`:

```dart
Text('nav.library'.tr())
AppText.titleLarge('nav.library')          // translates its key internally
'library.removed'.tr(namedArgs: {'count': '$n'})
```

No generated `LocaleKeys` — keys resolve at runtime. Proper nouns (source names)
are not translated.
